cff-version: 1.2.0
message: >-
  If you use this dashboard in scientific work, please cite the software
  entry below. When citing a specific dataset or figure, also cite the
  snapshot date that appears in the dashboard's About tab.
title: CAR-T Oncology Trials Monitor
type: software
authors:
  - family-names: Jeong
    given-names: Peter
    email: peter.jeong@uk-koeln.de
    affiliation: >-
      Klinik I für Innere Medizin, Hämatologie und Onkologie, Klinische
      Immunologie und Rheumatologie, Universitätsklinikum Köln
    orcid: null  # TODO: add ORCID if available
version: "1.0.0"
date-released: "2026-04-24"
repository-code: "https://github.com/ptjeong/ONC-CAR-T-Trials-Monitor"
url: "https://onc-car-t-trial-monitor.streamlit.app"
license: MIT
abstract: >-
  An interactive Streamlit dashboard that tracks CAR-T, CAR-NK, CAAR-T, and
  CAR-γδ T clinical trials across hematologic and solid tumors, sourced
  from the ClinicalTrials.gov v2 API. Provides a three-tier disease
  ontology (Branch → Category → Entity), cascading filters, antigen-target
  and product-type classification via a hybrid rule + calibrated-default +
  LLM-validation pipeline, cell-therapy modality annotation, approved-
  product overlays (FDA, NMPA, EMA), geographic mapping with country-
  selectable deep-dives, and eight publication-ready figures with
  provenance-tagged CSV exports.
keywords:
  - CAR-T
  - chimeric antigen receptor T cells
  - CAR-NK
  - oncology
  - hematologic malignancies
  - solid tumors
  - clinical trials
  - ClinicalTrials.gov
  - dashboard
  - streamlit
